'''Dr Jekyll''' is a [[random event]] NPC that appears and urgently asks the player for help making a potion. If talked to, he requests a cleaned [[herb]] of the player. If the player has a herb in their inventory, he will take it and give them a [[potions|potion]], but if the player has no herbs he will give the player a [[Strength potion|Strength potion(2)]] before disappearing. If the player has multiple herbs in their inventory, Dr Jekyll will only take one.

[[File:Dr_Jekyll_transforms.gif|thumb|left|Dr Jekyll transforms into Mr Hyde.]]
Before the [[Update:Optional Randoms & Goblins|Optional Randoms &amp; Goblins]] update, if ignored, Dr Jekyll would turn into Mr Hyde (level 14–159, depending on the player's [[Combat level]]) and attack the player with [[Melee]]. If killed, he would drop a potion or an empty [[vial]]. Killing him could sometimes be more profitable than giving him a herb, as he could possibly drop a [[Super restore|Super restore potion(4)]].

As with all random events, if a player goes into a zone that doesn't allow random events, such as banks, or boss rooms, Dr Jekyll will disappear.

